    "content": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n    <title>Agentic Coding Research Report - 2026-03-04</title>\n    <style>\n        * {\n            margin: 0;\n            padding: 0;\n            box-sizing: border-box;\n        }\n\n        body {\n            font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\n            font-size: 13px;\n            line-height: 1.5;\n            background-color: #f6f6ef;\n            color: #000000;\n            padding: 10px;\n        }\n\n        .container {\n            max-width: 1400px;\n            margin: 0 auto;\n            background-color: #f6f6ef;\n        }\n\n        header {\n            background-color: #ff6600;\n            padding: 8px 12px;\n            margin-bottom: 15px;\n        }\n\n        header h1 {\n            font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\n            font-size: 16px;\n            font-weight: bold;\n            color: #000000;\n        }\n\n        header .date {\n            font-size: 11px;\n            color: #000000;\n            margin-top: 4px;\n        }\n\n        .three-column-layout {\n            display: grid;\n            grid-template-columns: 40% 35% 25%;\n            gap: 15px;\n            margin-bottom: 20px;\n        }\n\n        @media (max-width: 1200px) {\n            .three-column-layout {\n                grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;\n            }\n\n            .technical-insights {\n                grid-column: 1 / -1;\n            }\n        }\n\n        @media (max-width: 768px) {\n            .three-column-layout {\n                grid-template-columns: 1fr;\n            }\n        }\n\n        .column {\n            background-color: #ffffff;\n            border: 1px solid #d4d4d4;\n            border-radius: 3px;\n            padding: 12px;\n        }\n\n        .column-header {\n            font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\n            font-size: 14px;\n            font-weight: bold;\n            color: #000000;\n            padding-bottom: 8px;\n            margin-bottom: 12px;\n            border-bottom: 2px solid #ff6600;\n        }\n\n        .item {\n            margin-bottom: 16px;\n            padding-bottom: 12px;\n            border-bottom: 1px solid #eeeeee;\n        }\n\n        .item:last-child {\n            border-bottom: none;\n            margin-bottom: 0;\n            padding-bottom: 0;\n        }\n\n        .item-title {\n            font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\n            font-size: 13px;\n            font-weight: bold;\n            margin-bottom: 6px;\n        }\n\n        .item-title a {\n            color: #000000;\n            text-decoration: none;\n        }\n\n        .item-title a:hover {\n            color: #ff6600;\n        }\n\n        .item-title a:visited {\n            color: #828282;\n        }\n\n        .item-description {\n            color: #000000;\n            margin-bottom: 6px;\n            line-height: 1.4;\n        }\n\n        .item-meta {\n            font-size: 11px;\n            color: #828282;\n        }\n\n        .item-meta a {\n            color: #828282;\n            text-decoration: none;\n        }\n\n        .item-meta a:hover {\n            color: #ff6600;\n        }\n\n        .tag {\n            display: inline-block;\n            background-color: #f6f6ef;\n            color: #828282;\n            padding: 2px 6px;\n            font-size: 10px;\n            border-radius: 2px;\n            margin-right: 4px;\n            margin-top: 4px;\n        }\n\n        .source-badge {\n            display: inline-block;\n            background-color: #ff6600;\n            color: #ffffff;\n            padding: 1px 5px;\n            font-size: 10px;\n            border-radius: 2px;\n            margin-left: 6px;\n        }\n\n        .insight-type {\n            font-size: 10px;\n            color: #ff6600;\n            text-transform: uppercase;\n            font-weight: bold;\n            margin-bottom: 4px;\n        }\n\n        .empty-state {\n            text-align: center;\n            padding: 30px 20px;\n            color: #828282;\n            font-style: italic;\n        }\n\n        footer {\n            text-align: center;\n            padding: 15px;\n            color: #828282;\n            font-size: 11px;\n            border-top: 1px solid #d4d4d4;\n            margin-top: 20px;\n        }\n\n        footer a {\n            color: #828282;\n            text-decoration: none;\n        }\n\n        footer a:hover {\n            color: #ff6600;\n        }\n\n        .feedback-quote {\n            background-color: #f6f6ef;\n            padding: 6px 8px;\n            margin-top: 6px;\n            font-size: 11px;\n            border-left: 3px solid #ff6600;\n            font-style: italic;\n        }\n\n        .feedback-source {\n            display: block;\n            font-size: 10px;\n            color: #828282;\n            margin-top: 4px;\n            font-style: normal;\n        }\n\n        .update-type {\n            display: inline-block;\n            font-size: 10px;\n            padding: 1px 5px;\n            border-radius: 2px;\n            margin-right: 4px;\n            text-transform: uppercase;\n            font-weight: bold;\n        }\n\n        .update-type.release {\n            background-color: #ffeaa7;\n            color: #d63031;\n        }\n\n        .update-type.feature {\n            background-color: #d1f2eb;\n            color: #1e8449;\n        }\n\n        @media print {\n            body {\n                background-color: #ffffff;\n            }\n\n            .column {\n                break-inside: avoid;\n            }\n\n            header {\n                background-color: #ffffff;\n                border-bottom: 2px solid #ff6600;\n            }\n\n            header h1, header .date {\n                color: #000000;\n            }\n        }\n    </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n    <div class=\"container\">\n        <header>\n            <h1>Agentic Coding Research Report</h1>\n            <div class=\"date\">2026-03-04 | Daily Update</div>\n        </header>\n\n        <main class=\"three-column-layout\">\n            <!-- New Products Section -->\n            <section class=\"column new-products\">\n                <div class=\"column-header\">New Products</div>\n                <div class=\"empty-state\">\n                    No new products discovered in this research cycle.\n                </div>\n            </section>\n\n            <!-- Whitelist Updates Section -->\n            <section class=\"column whitelist-updates\">\n                <div class=\"column-header\">Product Updates</div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://github.com/anthropics/claude-code/releases/tag/v2.1.63\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n                            Claude Code v2.1.63\n                        </a>\n                        <span class=\"update-type release\">Release</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Added /simplify and /batch bundled slash commands, HTTP hooks for external integrations, and extensive memory leak fixes across the platform (20+ fixes).\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        2026-02-28\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://github.com/continuedev/continue/releases\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n                            Continue v1.3.32\n                        </a>\n                        <span class=\"update-type feature\">Feature</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Added limited MCP App support, cn checks CLI command, enabled agent mode for LM Studio models, updated default model to Claude Opus 4.6.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        2026-02-27\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://cursor.com/changelog\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n                            Cursor Cloud Agents with Computer Use\n                        </a>\n                        <span class=\"update-type feature\">Feature</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Cloud agents can now use the software they create to test changes and demo their work, producing merge-ready PRs with artifacts (videos, screenshots, and logs).\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        2026-02-26\n                        <div class=\"feedback-quote\">\"A new era has begun - Cloud Agents break previous limitations\"<span class=\"feedback-source\">CSDN</span></div>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://cursor.com/changelog\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n                            Cursor Bugbot Autofix\n                        </a>\n                        <span class=\"update-type feature\">Feature</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Bugbot can automatically fix issues in pull requests using cloud agents in isolated VMs. 35% of autofix changes are merged. Resolution rate increased from 52% to 76%.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        2026-02-26\n                        <div class=\"feedback-quote\">\"You submit a PR, wake up the next morning, and Bugbot has already fixed 10 small issues\"<span class=\"feedback-source\">51CTO</span></div>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://github.com/anthropics/claude-code/releases/tag/v2.1.59\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n                            Claude Code v2.1.59\n                        </a>\n                        <span class=\"update-type feature\">Feature</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Claude automatically saves useful context to auto-memory with /memory management. Added /copy command with interactive picker for code blocks.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        2026-02-26\n                        <div class=\"feedback-quote\">\"How to turn it off - the most discussed topic was disabling auto memory\"<span class=\"feedback-source\">Reddit</span></div>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/releases\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n                            Aider v0.86.0\n                        </a>\n                        <span class=\"update-type release\">Release</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Added support for all GPT-5 models, Grok-4 via xAI, Gemini 2.5 Flash Lite Preview, and UI improvements including /clear confirmation.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        2026-02-23\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://claude.ai/code\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n                            Claude Code Security Module\n                        </a>\n                        <span class=\"update-type feature\">Feature</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Automated scanning with human-like analysis to identify business logic defects, access control issues, and security vulnerabilities. Uses multi-stage verification.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        2026-02-20\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://geminicli.com/docs/changelogs/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n                            Gemini 3.1 Pro\n                        </a>\n                        <span class=\"update-type release\">Release</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Stronger code generation, more stable agent performance, 1M-2M+ token context. 77.4% on SWE-bench Verified. Free for all users.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        2026-02-19\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://cursor.sh/changelog\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n                            Cursor Slack Background Agents\n                        </a>\n                        <span class=\"update-type feature\">Feature</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Launch agents directly from Slack by mentioning @Cursor. Agents can read threads, understand context, and create PRs without leaving the conversation.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        2026-02-19\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n            </section>\n\n            <!-- Technical Insights Section -->\n            <section class=\"column technical-insights\">\n                <div class=\"column-header\">Technical Insights</div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"insight-type\">Opinion</div>\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Mar/4/qwen/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n                            Something is afoot in the land of Qwen\n                        </a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Simon Willison discusses Qwen 3.5 and concerns about potential high-profile departures from Alibaba's Qwen team. Highlights the rapidly evolving Chinese AI landscape.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        Simon Willison | 2026-03-04\n                    </div>\n                    <div>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">AI</span>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">LLMs</span>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">Qwen</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"insight-type\">Opinion</div>\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/guides/agentic-engineering-patterns/anti-patterns/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n                            Don't inflict unreviewed code on collaborators\n                        </a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Simon Willison identifies a key anti-pattern: filing PRs with code you haven't reviewed. Developers must review agent-generated code before submitting to maintain quality.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        Simon Willison | 2026-03-04\n                    </div>\n                    <div>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">AI ethics</span>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">code review</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"insight-type\">Discussion</div>\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Mar/3/donald-knuth/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n                            Donald Knuth on Claude Opus 4.6\n                        </a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Donald Knuth expressed surprise that Claude Opus 4.6 solved an open problem he'd been working on for weeks. A significant moment in AI adoption.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        Donald Knuth | 2026-03-03\n                    </div>\n                    <div>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">Claude</span>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">problem solving</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"insight-type\">Technical</div>\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Mar/3/gemini-31-flash-lite/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n                            Gemini 3.1 Flash-Lite: Ultra-low-cost model\n                        </a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Google released Gemini 3.1 Flash-Lite at $0.25/million input tokens - 1/8th the price of Gemini 3.1 Pro. Continues the trend of increasingly affordable AI models.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        Simon Willison | 2026-03-03\n                    </div>\n                    <div>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">Google</span>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">pricing</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"insight-type\">Technical</div>\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/guides/agentic-engineering-patterns/gif-optimization/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n                            GIF optimization tool using WebAssembly\n                        </a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Simon Willison built a GIF optimizer using Gifsicle compiled to WebAssembly, with a web interface for visually previewing and comparing different settings.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        Simon Willison | 2026-03-02\n                    </div>\n                    <div>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">WebAssembly</span>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">tools</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"insight-type\">Technical</div>\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Mar/1/claude-import-memory/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n                            Anthropic's memory import feature is just a prompt\n                        </a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Simon discovered that Anthropic's \"import your memories\" feature is actually just a prompt. Reveals a pattern where AI features use clever prompting rather than infrastructure.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        Simon Willison | 2026-03-01\n                    </div>\n                    <div>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">prompt engineering</span>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">memory</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"insight-type\">Opinion</div>\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/guides/agentic-engineering-patterns/interactive-explanations/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n                            Interactive explanations and cognitive debt\n                        </a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Simon discusses \"cognitive debt\" - losing track of how agent-written code works. Advocates for interactive explanations to maintain understanding of agent-generated code.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        Simon Willison | 2026-02-28\n                    </div>\n                    <div>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">cognitive debt</span>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">explorables</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"insight-type\">Opinion</div>\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://minimaxir.com/2026/02/ai-agent-coding/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n                            AI skeptic becomes believer after testing agents\n                        </a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Max Woolf's account of porting Python's scikit-learn to Rust using agents. Notes Opus 4.6/Codex 5.3 are \"an order of magnitude better than coding LLMs released just months before.\"\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        Max Woolf | 2026-02-27\n                    </div>\n                    <div>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">Rust</span>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">agentic engineering</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"insight-type\">Technical</div>\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://claude.com/contact-sales/claude-for-oss\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n                            Free Claude Max for open source maintainers\n                        </a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Anthropic offering Claude Max 20x plan ($200/month) free for 6 months to OSS maintainers with 5,000+ GitHub stars or 1M+ monthly NPM downloads.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        Anthropic | 2026-02-27\n                    </div>\n                    <div>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">open-source</span>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">Claude</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"insight-type\">Opinion</div>\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://twitter.com/karpathy/status/2026731645169185220\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n                            Andrej Karpathy: Programming changed in December\n                        </a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        \"Coding agents basically didn't work before December and basically work since.\" Models now have higher quality, long-term coherence and can power through large tasks.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        Andrej Karpathy | 2026-02-26\n                    </div>\n                    <div>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">agentic engineering</span>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">inflection</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"insight-type\">Technical</div>\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://trufflesecurity.com/blog/google-api-keys-werent-secrets-but-then-gemini-changed-the-rules\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n                            Google API Keys security vulnerability\n                        </a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Google Maps and Gemini share the same API keys. Maps keys are public but Gemini keys can access private files. Truffle found 2,863 API keys that could access Gemini.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        Truffle Security | 2026-02-26\n                    </div>\n                    <div>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">security</span>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">Gemini</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"insight-type\">Technical</div>\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Feb/27/unicode-explorer/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n                            Unicode Explorer using HTTP range requests\n                        </a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Simon built a Unicode Explorer using binary search over HTTP Range requests against a 76.6MB file. Visualizes each step of the binary search with fetch times.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        Simon Willison | 2026-02-27\n                    </div>\n                    <div>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">HTTP</span>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">algorithms</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n            </section>\n        </main>\n\n        <footer>\n            <p>Report generated by <a href=\"https://github.com/anthropics/agentdaily\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Agent Code Daily</a> - Powered by <a href=\"https://claude.com/code\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Claude Agent SDK</a></p>\n            <p style=\"margin-top: 8px;\">Last updated: 2026-03-04 00:06:59 UTC</p>\n        </footer>\n    </div>\n</body>\n</html>\n",
