          "+                        <a href=\"https://twitter.com/karpathy/status/2026731645169185220\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">",
          "+                            Andrej Karpathy: Programming changed in December",
          "+                        </a>",
          "                     </div>",
          "+                    <div class=\"item-description\">",
          "+                        \"Coding agents basically didn't work before December and basically work since.\" Models now have higher quality, long-term coherence and can power through large tasks.",
          "+                    </div>",
          "+                    <div class=\"item-meta\">",
          "+                        Andrej Karpathy | 2026-02-26",
          "+                    </div>",
          "+                    <div>",
          "+                        <span class=\"tag\">agentic engineering</span>",
          "+                        <span class=\"tag\">inflection</span>",
          "+                    </div>",
          "+                </div>",
          " ",
          "-                    <div class=\"item\">",
          "-                        <div class=\"item-title\">",
          "-                            <a href=\"https://github.com/anthropics/claude-code/releases/tag/v2.1.59\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">",
          "-                                Claude Code v2.1.59: Auto-memory and /copy command",
          "-                            </a>",
          "-                        </div>",
          "-                        <div class=\"item-description\">",
          "-                            Claude Code v2.1.59 introduced auto-memory where Claude automatically saves useful context to auto-memory with /memory management, plus /copy command with interactive picker for code blocks. Community feedback was mixed: positive for solving cross-session memory pain points, but negative for performance issues and unwanted memory writing behavior.",
          "-                        </div>",
          "-                        <div class=\"item-meta\">",
          "-                            <span class=\"update-type feature\">Feature</span>",
          "-                            <a href=\"https://github.com/anthropics/claude-code/releases/tag/v2.1.59\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Read More</a>",
          "-                        </div>",
          "-                        <div class=\"topics\">",
          "-                            <span class=\"topic\">AI coding</span>",
          "-                            <span class=\"topic\">Claude Code</span>",
          "-                            <span class=\"topic\">memory management</span>",
          "-                            <span class=\"topic\">context management</span>",
          "-                        </div>",
          "+                <div class=\"item\">",
          "+                    <div class=\"insight-type\">Technical</div>",
          "+                    <div class=\"item-title\">",
          "+                        <a href=\"https://trufflesecurity.com/blog/google-api-keys-werent-secrets-but-then-gemini-changed-the-rules\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">",
          "+                            Google API Keys security vulnerability",
          "+                        </a>",
          "                     </div>",
          "+                    <div class=\"item-description\">",
          "+                        Google Maps and Gemini share the same API keys. Maps keys are public but Gemini keys can access private files. Truffle found 2,863 API keys that could access Gemini.",
          "+                    </div>",
          "+                    <div class=\"item-meta\">",
          "+                        Truffle Security | 2026-02-26",
          "+                    </div>",
          "+                    <div>",
          "+                        <span class=\"tag\">security</span>",
          "+                        <span class=\"tag\">Gemini</span>",
          "+                    </div>",
          "+                </div>",
          " ",
          "+                <div class=\"item\">",
          "+                    <div class=\"insight-type\">Technical</div>",
          "+                    <div class=\"item-title\">",
          "+                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Feb/27/unicode-explorer/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">",
          "+                            Unicode Explorer using HTTP range requests",
          "+                        </a>",
          "+                    </div>",
          "+                    <div class=\"item-description\">",
          "+                        Simon built a Unicode Explorer using binary search over HTTP Range requests against a 76.6MB file. Visualizes each step of the binary search with fetch times.",
          "+                    </div>",
          "+                    <div class=\"item-meta\">",
          "+                        Simon Willison | 2026-02-27",
          "+                    </div>",
          "+                    <div>",
          "+                        <span class=\"tag\">HTTP</span>",
          "+                        <span class=\"tag\">algorithms</span>",
          "+                    </div>",
          "                 </div>",
          "+",
          "             </section>",
          "         </main>",
          " ",
          "         <footer>",
          "-            <a href=\"#\">Archive</a>",
          "-            <a href=\"#\">About</a>",
          "-            <a href=\"#\">RSS Feed</a>",
          "-            <a href=\"#\">GitHub</a>",
          "-            <p style=\"margin-top: 10px; font-size: 8pt;\">Generated with Claude Code • Data updated daily</p>",
          "+            <p>Report generated by <a href=\"https://github.com/anthropics/agentdaily\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Agent Code Daily</a> - Powered by <a href=\"https://claude.com/code\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Claude Agent SDK</a></p>",
          "+            <p style=\"margin-top: 8px;\">Last updated: 2026-03-04 00:06:59 UTC</p>",
